-Provide an alternative to string concatenation
-Allow us to insert variables into a string
-AKA:
  -Template literals
  -String templates

With a template we can create one string and insert the variable values by surrounding them with ${}

Ex.)

const lastName = "Reilly";
const firstName = "Michael";
const middleName = "Edward";


console.log(`${lastName}, ${firstName} ${middleName}`);

Any Javascript that returns a value can be added to a template string between the ${} in a template string

Template strings honor whitespace making it easier to draft up email templates, code examples, or anything else that contains whitespace. You can have a string
that spans multiple lines without breaking your code:

